# FILE: .git-blame-ignore-revs
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# üåç World Discovery Engine (WDE) ‚Äî Git Blame Ignore Revisions
#
# Purpose:
#   This file lists commit SHAs where large-scale *mechanical changes* were made
#   (formatting, linting, dependency bumps, auto-generated scaffolds).
#
#   By ignoring these commits, `git blame` remains focused on *semantic changes*
#   (new features, bugfixes, scientific logic), instead of line rewraps or style-only updates.
#
# Usage:
#   git config blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs
#   # or globally:
#   git config --global blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs
#
# Guidelines:
#   - Include only commits that don‚Äôt alter semantics (e.g. Black, Ruff, isort, Prettier runs).
#   - Do NOT include functional changes (pipeline logic, config updates).
#   - Add new SHAs with a clear comment explaining what was done.
#
# References:
#   https://git-scm.com/docs/git-blame#Documentation/git-blame.txt---ignore-revs-fileltfilegt
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

